The paper deals with algorithms for polynomial evaluation, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The use of sublinear amortized cost per point suggests that the paper may belong to the computational complexity (cs.CC) or data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. The fact that the paper deals with bivariate polynomials suggests that it may also belong to the computational geometry (cs.CG) sub-category. The use of arithmetic operations suggests that the paper may also belong to the scientific computing (cs.SC) sub-category. Finally, the use of polynomials in control systems suggests that the paper may also belong to the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category.
